data.value:
Tips for Preventing Spam Delivery
1) Make sure that the subject length does not exceed 40 characters. --------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 2) Do not use / repeat unnecessary and multiple punctuation marks on the subject. --------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 3) If the mail you send is not very formal or does not belong to a private institution, add "RE:" to the beginning of the subject. Although this is not common, it prevents it from being detected as "Replied Mail" by the servers and entering the spam folder. --------------------------------------------------- ------------------------------ 4) Before the message you will write in the Mail section, add links such as "If You Do Not Want to Receive This Mail Click ..." or "Click If You Want To Exit Our Mailing List" so that the users do not want to receive the mail you send, instead of marking it as spam. so they can choose this. -------------------------------------------------- ------------------------------ 5) Avoid adding too many links and images to your mail content. Otherwise it can be annoying for the recipient to wait for the pictures to open and mark them as spam. --------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 6) Sending to more than one e-mail address at a time may cause your address to be marked as spam by mail servers. Therefore, the e-mail method we use in the system sends each e-mail to a single user, but repeats this process over and over. --------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 7) There must be a certain period of time between the e-mails you send. More than one mail sent on top of each other can cause you to be marked as spam by your server. By using the "Send Periodically" method we have provided to you, you will reduce your e-mail address from being marked as spam even a bit. --------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 8) Choose your target audience correctly. This is a big factor for the other party not to mark the mail they receive from you as spam. For example, you will send make-up, special care, etc. to men in your mailing list. football, sports, etc. that you will send to women. Mails can be viewed as annoying and your mail may be marked as spam. That's why you can filter by gender using the simple filtering tool. Issues such as the remaining interests are the choices you should take care of while developing your mailing lists. --------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 9) You can check whether your servers are taken to spam lists from black list sites, which you can find in many places on the internet about mail servers, and you can succeed in getting out of these lists after effective dialogue with your mail servers.

data.name: RichTextBox6.Text
data.value:
Mail Sending Settings: In this field, you must enter the settings of your e-mail that you will send. -------------------------------------------------- ------------------------------ Your E-Mail Address: Enter the address from which you will send the e-mails in this field. -------------------------------------------------- ------------------------------ Password: Enter the password of your e-mail. -------------------------------------------------- ------------------------------ Name or Title: Enter your name, title or company name that will be displayed by the recipients when your mails are sent. (Enter the registered name to the e-mail address you use to reduce the risk of spam) -------------------------------------------------- ------------------------------ Your SMTP Server: Select which server the address you send mails to uses. For example: If you will send from sample@hotmail.com, select smtp.live.com. Again, in this section, if you are going to send an e-mail via your website, you should select "Enter Manually" option and enter your SMTP address and the port you will send to. (If you don't know the SMTP settings, contact your domain provider)
NOTE: Since personal website mails do not support SSL, SSL is not available in that option. If you have a mail server that supports SSL, contact us and we will activate this area specifically for you. -------------------------------------------------- ------------------------------ Periodic Sending Settings: When you use the "Send" button on the "Send Mail" screen, you can set the time to be added between mails from this section. -------------------------------------------------- ------------------------------ The Signature You Want to Add to the Message: When you select the HTML section of the "Send Mail" screen, you can edit the signature that will be added to the sent e-mail when you check the box for adding signature. Here, too, the simple toolbar will make it easy for you to add HTML code fragments that you will use.

data.name: RichTextBox5.Text
data.value: Add Contact: You need to use this field to add new people to the list. In order for your Private Fields to be forwarded to the other party without error, please fill in as requested from you. -------------------------------------------------- ------------------------------ View & Delete Contacts: All the contacts you add are listed as name, gender and e-mail address. If you wish, you can choose an option as "Men Only" or "Women Only" to reduce the risk of spam. -------------------------------------------------- ------------------------------ Delete Selected Contact: If you have a user you want to remove from your mailing list, select it from the list and use this button to delete it without any problems. (The List is Automatically Ordered Alphabetically.)
